\ element-wise matrix division by an all-nonzero divisor works
[ 4 6 8 10 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 2 3 4 5 ] 2 2 matrix  / .

\ a zero anywhere in the divisor is an error, matching the scalar path
[ 1 2 3 4 ] 2 2 matrix  [ 1 0 2 2 ] 2 2 matrix  /
\ zero in the first cell
[ 1 2 ] 1 2 matrix  [ 0 1 ] 1 2 matrix  /

\ scalar divide-by-zero is also an error (existing behavior, shown for contrast)
6 0 /
\ scalar nonzero divide still works
6 3 / .
